<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="79" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[136,1452,1202,2021]" pageId="6" pageNumber="79">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,265,1706,1732]" pageId="6" pageNumber="79">Notes:</emphasis>
—In the phylogenetic analyses, our new collection (MFLUCC 21−0153) clustered with the ex-type strain of 
<taxonomicName box="[166,400,1742,1768]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Microascaceae" genus="Periconia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Microascales" pageId="6" pageNumber="79" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="epilithographicola">
<emphasis box="[166,400,1742,1768]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="79">P. epilithographicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(CBS 144017) with high statistical supports (100% ML/1.00 PP, 
<figureCitation box="[1127,1191,1742,1768]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[136,229,1920,1942]" captionTargetBox="[202,1397,333,1893]" captionTargetId="figure-81@4.[183,1404,314,1893]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. Phylogenetic tree generated from a maximum likelihood analysis based on a concatenated alignment of ITS, LSU, SSU, and TEF1-α sequences data in Periconiaceae. The tree is rooted with Morosphaeria ramunculicola (KH220) and M. velatispora (KH221). Bootstrap support values equal to or higher than 70% ML (left) or posterior probability values equal to or higher than 0.90 Bayesian PP (right) are indicated on the nodes. The newly generated sequences are in red, and type strains are in black/red bold." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6875703" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6875703/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="79">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). Morphologically, our new isolate is identical to 
<taxonomicName box="[430,666,1778,1804]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Microascaceae" genus="Periconia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Microascales" pageId="6" pageNumber="79" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="epilithographicola">
<emphasis box="[430,666,1778,1804]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="79">P. epilithographicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(CBS 144017) except for longer conidiophores the ex-type (252–270 µm). Nucleotide comparisons showed that there is 1 bp out of 554 bp in 
<collectionCode box="[975,1017,1814,1840]" pageId="6" pageNumber="79">ITS</collectionCode>
sequence difference between the new isolate and 
<taxonomicName box="[263,499,1850,1876]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Microascaceae" genus="Periconia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Microascales" pageId="6" pageNumber="79" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="epilithographicola">
<emphasis box="[263,499,1850,1876]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="79">P. epilithographicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(CBS 144017). Thus, we identified the new isolate as 
<taxonomicName box="[1110,1345,1850,1876]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Microascaceae" genus="Periconia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Microascales" pageId="6" pageNumber="79" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="epilithographicola">
<emphasis box="[1110,1345,1850,1876]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="79">P. epilithographicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on phylogenetic analyses and morphological characteristics.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[136,1452,1202,2021]" pageId="6" pageNumber="79">
<taxonomicName box="[189,516,1922,1948]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Microascaceae" genus="Periconia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Microascales" pageId="6" pageNumber="79" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="epilithographicola">
<emphasis box="[189,516,1922,1948]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="79">Periconia epilithographicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was originally isolated from 19 
<superScript attach="left" box="[876,889,1922,1936]" fontSize="6" pageId="6" pageNumber="79">th</superScript>
century art lamina in 
<collectingCountry box="[1139,1261,1922,1948]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="6" pageNumber="79">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Coronado-Ruiz, C. &amp; Avendano, R. &amp; Escudero-Leyva, E. &amp; Conejo-Barboza, G. &amp; Chaverri, P. &amp; Chavarria, M." pageId="6" pageNumber="79" pagination="1 - 9" refId="ref6061" refString="Coronado-Ruiz, C., Avendano, R., Escudero-Leyva, E., Conejo-Barboza, G., Chaverri, P. &amp; Chavarria, M. (2018) Two new cellulolytic fungal species isolated from a 19 th-century art collection. Scientific Reports 8: 1 - 9. https: // doi. org / 10.1038 / s 41598 - 018 - 24934 - 7" type="journal article" year="2018">
Coronado-Ruiz 
<emphasis box="[136,193,1958,1984]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="79">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
), while the new isolate was collected from 
<taxonomicName box="[750,938,1959,1985]" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Ananas" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="6" pageNumber="79" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="comosus">
<emphasis box="[750,938,1959,1985]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="79">Ananas comosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[975,1078,1958,1984]" name="Thailand" pageId="6" pageNumber="79">Thailand</collectingCountry>
. Therefore, 
<taxonomicName box="[1215,1451,1958,1984]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Microascaceae" genus="Periconia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Microascales" pageId="6" pageNumber="79" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="epilithographicola">
<emphasis box="[1215,1451,1958,1984]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="79">P. epilithographicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(MFLUCC 21−0153) is growing on a new host and is a new geographic record.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
